<section class="card">
  <h2>Why Conditions May Differ Near You</h2>

  <p>
    Provincial medians smooth out local extremes.
    Cold air drainage, valley floors, slope orientation, and urban heat
    can all shift frost timing compared to the regional average.
  </p>

  <p>
    If you garden in a sheltered or elevated location,
    your effective growing season may be shorter or longer
    than the provincial median suggests.
  </p>

